  "body": "# Feature Issue\r\n\r\nBlur the top bar background.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46027/194842851-5aeeedf8-d769-4331-acd1-22f0cb808132.png\" height=\"400\" />\r\n\r\n### Notes\r\n\r\nThis issue might not be as simple as it looks, given that `@react-native-community/blur` can be tricky to get the desired effect. When the `BlurView` component first renders, it takes a snapshot of what's on screen, but this sometimes leads to halo artifacts around things that are on top of the blur and should not be blurred. Take a look at the `status-im.switcher.switcher/switcher-screen` component, it seems to work fine there, possibly because the animation delays the final output, and so the snapshot is taken correctly.\r\n\r\nExample code (incomplete or incorrect):\r\n\r\n```clojure\r\n[react/blur-view {:style         {:height           \"100%\"\r\n                                  :width            \"100%\"\r\n                                  :position         :absolute\r\n                                  :top              0\r\n                                  :left             0\r\n                                  :background-color :transparent}\r\n                  :blur-amount   20\r\n                  :overlay-color :transparent}]\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Resources\r\n\r\n- https://www.figma.com/file/eDfxTa9IoaCMUy5cLTp0ys/Shell-for-Mobile?node-id=451%3A18681\r\n",
